  "label": "Cairnspire Massif",
  "description": "Cairnspire Massif forms a dominant basaltic uplift on Brineshade, its steep faces banded with pale halite seams that read as sharp white striations under Saltharrow’s hard radiance. Knife-edged ridgelines enclose wind-scoured saddles where mineral haze condenses into crusted rime along shaded clefts. Extensive talus fans of black rock descend to surrounding saline flats, creating stark tonal boundaries used as fixed sighting references in surface navigation. Subsurface surveys register persistent tidal microfracturing aligned with the system’s pronounced gravitic gradients.",
